item.title: This is with pi(need a good helper)
item.dc:creator: @zyle1992 Zymus
item.description:
@zyle1992 wrote:

  1. There is no legitimate reason as to why you would need someone’s password to their account.
  2. If you wanted to check if someone was duping items, I’m sure a competent programmer like yourself could make a command that temporarily changed your inventory, bank, and equipment items to the items of the character you’re checking.
  3. Disabling authentication would only make the people pissed off in your server. People would be stealing other people’s items, etc. OR You disable it incorrectly, resulting in “Invalid username or password” being sent to the clients, again pissing them off. OR You semi-disable it, letting people log in correctly, but the server doesn’t save the password to the file, again making it point less.
  4. There is a very simple way to do what you want to do with a slight bit of common sense, but no self-respecting member of this community would tell it to you.
